{{Quote|The Jedi set a trap. They lured us into battle against a small Republic fleet. During the attack a team of Jedi Knights boarded your ship. The Jedi strike team captured you and the Council used the Force to reprogram your mind; they wiped away your identity and turned you against your own followers.|Darth Malak to Revan|<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic" />}}
The '''Capture of Darth Revan''' was a vital mission carried out by the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] during the [[Jedi Civil War]].

==History==
===The trap===
{{Quote|You cannot win, Revan!|Bastila Shan, moments before Revan's apparent death|<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic" />}}
Overwhelmed by [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] invasion forces commanded by the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the]] [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Revan/Legends|Darth Revan]], the Republic and the [[Jedi Council/Legends|Jedi Council]] knew that they could not hold out forever against the seemingly infinite Sith fleet. In desperation, they drafted a daring plan to deprive the Sith of their powerful and charismatic leader. By carrying out their scheme, they hoped to end the war prematurely by destabilizing the fledgling [[Darth Revan's Sith Empire|Sith Empire]] and giving the [[Republic Military/Legends|Republic Military]] time to rally its forces.<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic" /><ref name="Chronicles of the Old Republic">{{LucasArts|url=games/swkotor_sithlords|text=''Chronicles of the Old Republic''|int=Chronicles of the Old Republic}}</ref>

In the year [[3957 BBY]], the Republic set a trap for Revan. A small Republic fleet was sent to the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]] to act as bait. A contingent of Jedi commanded by [[Bastila Shan]] accompanied the fleet and led the mission. The Jedi Council's gamble paid off when a Sith fleet commanded by Darth Revan himself engaged the small Republic force.<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic" /><ref name="Chronicles of the Old Republic" /><ref name="The New Essential Chronology">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref>

[[File:Bastilasstriketeamfacesrevan.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Bastila Shan and her strike team face Darth Revan.]]

Amidst the resulting fleet battle, Bastila Shan's [[Jedi strike team (Capture of Darth Revan)|strike team]], made up of a mixed force of Republic military personnel and Jedi, managed to board [[Darth Revan's flagship]] and battle their way to the command deck. It is unknown how many Jedi were originally in the task force but at least four made it along with at least one Republic soldier to the bridge to engage Revan and his acolytes. Seemingly undaunted, Revan struck down all who approached him. Standing on the command deck of his vessel, Revan [[Telekinesis/Legends#Choking_powers|Force choked]] the Republic soldier before readying himself to duel Bastila and her few remaining companions.<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic" /><ref name="Chronicles of the Old Republic" /><ref name="The New Essential Chronology" />

===Darth Malak's betrayal===
{{Quote|I ordered my own ships to fire on your bridge. I thought I could destroy all my enemies with a single glorious victory! I never dreamed the Jedi would take you alive from the wreckage.|Darth Malak to Revan|audio=MalakFiredonRevan.flac|<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic" />}}
[[File:Malak-betrays-Revan.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Malak watches as his ships open fire on Revan's cruiser.]]In that moment of doubt, the ambitious Darth Malak, Revan's [[Sith apprentice/Legends|Sith apprentice]], decided that the time was right for his ascension to the rank of Dark Lord of the Sith. Seeing his chance to usurp his [[Sith Master/Legends|Master's]] title, Malak ordered his gunners to open fire upon the bridge of Revan's command ship, but all did not go as he had planned; the majority of the Jedi strike team was killed and Darth Revan's flag ship was destroyed, but Revan himself survived. The remaining Jedi captured the critically injured Dark Lord and escaped the ship prior to its destruction.<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic" /><ref name="Chronicles of the Old Republic" /><ref name="The New Essential Chronology" />

Bastila used the Force to save Revan's life, thus forming a powerful [[Force-bond/Legends|Force bond]] between them. The Jedi brought Revan before the [[Jedi Council/Legends|Jedi Council]] who rebuilt his broken mind with a new personality loyal to the Republic in an effort to mask his true identity. In so doing, they hoped that Revan's subconscious memories would lead them to the source of the Sith's seemingly endless supply of military hardware. With his aid, they would attempt to locate it and destroy it at any cost.<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic" /><ref name="Chronicles of the Old Republic" /><ref name="The New Essential Chronology" />

==Behind the scenes==
Though the video game ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]'' heavily implies that Bastila never actually engaged Revan in battle (Malak firing on Revan's ship just before such a fight could take place), an illustration from [[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']] depicts such a scene. It remains unclear whether or not the engagement actually occurred.

''The Betrayal of Darth Revan'' introduced a dark Jedi named Darth Voren, who leads a squad of troopers encountered by the Strike Team. Depending on the player's choice, he can be killed or persuaded to help by ordering other personnel away from the bridge.

